The '''Samsung Galaxy Tab A 10.5 (2018, LTE)''' ('''SM-T595''', codename '''gta2xllte''')
is an SDM450/MSM8953 tablet. It is brought up on the mainline kernel using the
generic [[Qualcomm Snapdragon 450 (qcom-msm8953)|qcom-msm8953]] pmOS device package
plus a device tree (''sdm450-samsung-gta2xllte''). The Wi-Fi-only sibling is the
SM-T590 (gta2xlwifi, SDA450).

{{note|This is an early/alpha mainline port. Display, Wi-Fi and Bluetooth work, but
the touchscreen does not yet (no mainline driver for the panel's ST fts1ba90a), and
the device hard-resets under very heavy eMMC write load (e.g. installing large
packages on-device) — see [[#Known issues]].}}

